@node Introduction "Introduction"

@{B}@{U}Introduction@{UB}@{UU}

   With Silver_Prefs you can set several parameters of the roleplaying-game
   system "Silver" and save these parameters in a configuration-file.

@endnode



@node Requirements "Requirements"

@{B}@{U}Requirements@{UB}@{UU}

   Silver_Prefs needs at least Kickstart 2.0 (V37).
   Also the
      gadtools.library	Version 37+  (beginning with Kickstart 2.0 in ROM)
   and
      reqtools.library	Version 38+  (contained in this archive)
   are required.


   ReqTools.library Copyright © Nico Francios, Magnus Holmgren

@endnode



@node Installation "Installation"

@{B}@{U}Installation@{UB}@{UU}

   Silver_Prefs has to be in the same directory as the silver mainprogram.

   The ReqTools.library has to be in the LIBS: directory.

@endnode



@node Usage "Usage"

@{B}@{U}Usage@{UB}@{UU}

   If there is no configuration-file, there will be a message and the silver
   @{"default values" link default} will be used.
   It appears following window:

   @{" temporary files " link dirdatin}@{"                       " link dirdatout}
   @{"   save games    " link dirdatin}@{"                       " link dirdatout}
   @{" adventure path  " link dirdatin}@{"                       " link dirdatout}
   @{"  documentation  " link dirdatin}@{"                       " link dirdatout}

   @{"   screen mode   " link bilddatin}@{"                       " link bilddatout}
   @{"      font       " link fontdatin}@{"                       " link fontdatout}

	 quick start @{"  " link quickstart}
	     no undo @{"  " link noundo}
	     degrade @{"  " link degrade}

   @{"create directory   " link makedir}       @{"default values" link default}

   @{"   save    " link save}   @{"  delete   " link delete}   @{"  cancel   " link cancel}

@endnode



@node dirdatin "directory for... :"

@{B}@{U}directory for... :@{UB}@{UU}

   A directory-requester appears. Select with the requester the directory for
   temporary files/save games/adventures/documentation.

@endnode



@node dirdatout "directory for... :"

@{B}@{U}directory for... :@{UB}@{UU}

   Here is the current path for temporary files/save games/adventures/
   documtation displayed.

@endnode



@node bilddatin "screen-mode"

@{B}@{U}screen mode@{UB}@{UU}

   A screen-mode-requester appears. There you select the screen mode
   Silver uses.

   Note:
      The screen has to be at least 256 lines high. The minimum width depends
      on the used font. If you select a to small screen there will be a
      message, that the screen is to small -> please select a different
      screen.
      You also have the choose between 16 or 32 colours. For 32 colours the
      AA (AGA)-chipset or a graphic-card is needed. With OCS or ECS only 16
      colours are possible.

@endnode



@node bilddatout "screen mode"

@{B}@{U}screnn mode@{UB}@{UU}

   Here is the current screen mode and the number of colours displayed.

@endnode



@node fontdatin "font"

@{B}@{U}font@{UB}@{UU}

   A font-requester appears. There you select the font Silver uses.

   Note:
      The maximum size of th font depends on the used screen-mode. If the
      selected font is to big there will be a message, that the font is to big
      -> please select a different font.

@endnode



@node fontdatout "font"

@{B}@{U}font@{UB}@{UU}

   Here is the current font displayed.

@endnode



@node quickstart "quickstart"

@{B}@{U}quickstart@{UB}@{UU}

   If this option is switched off, then after the start of a new game, all
   maps will be copied.
   If this option is switched on, the maps are copied when they are needed.

@endnode



@node noundo "no undo"

@{B}@{U}on undo@{UB}@{UU}

   If this is activited, the undo-buffer in the editor is switched off
   -> this saves memory

@endnode



@node degrade "degrade"

@{B}@{U}degrade@{UB}@{UU}

   If this is activited, the selection with listview-gadgets is switched off.
   This is useful, if the listview-selection is buggy (it hasn't been tested
   with OS2.0)

@endnode



@node makedir "create directory"

@{B}@{U}create directory@{UB}@{UU}

   If you want to create a directory, you can do this using Silver_Prefs.
   At first you enter the name of the directroy. After that you select with
   the directory-requester the placce for the new directory.

@endnode



@node default "default values"

@{B}@{U}default values@{UB}@{UU}

   The silver default values for paths, screen, font, etc. will be used.

@endnode



@node save "save"

@{B}@{U}save@{UB}@{UU}

   The configuration is saved and Silver_Prefs quits.

@endnode



@node delete "delete"

@{B}@{U}delete@{UB}@{UU}

   The configuration is deleted and Silver_Prefs quits.

@endnode



@node cancel "cancel"

@{B}@{U}cancel@{UB}@{UU}

   The program quits and the configuration is NOT saved.

@endnode



